    "Id": "chassisdef_ursa_URA-2A",
    "Name": "Ursa",
    "Details": "The suite of offensive weaponry carried by the Ursa is divided between the left and right torsos. On each side are a brace of Medium X-Pulse Laser, popular with those who regularly fought the Clans; mounted into the right torso is a Rotary AC/2 supplied with a ton of ammunition, while mounted into the left torso is an ER PPC. The MASC system built into the Ursa in combination with the 325 XL fusion engine that powers the 'Mech results in a ferocious quadrupedal design that can run at speeds of over 100 km/h; this, combined with the gyro and twelve and a half tons of armor meant that the Ursa can not only survive full-speed collisions but can do so without falling or the pilot losing control. This led to MechWarriors nicknamed the Ursa 'the Rhino' because of the brutal charges it can perform.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Quad Mech</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.09</color></b>",
